linear gradient: by default is top-bottom
background: linear-gradient(blue, yellow);

Can change it to horizontal:
background: linear-gradient(to right, blue, yellow);
background: linear-gradient(to left, blue, yellow);

for diagonal:
background: linear-gradient(to top right, blue, yellow);
background: linear-gradient(to bottom left, blue, yellow);

background: linear-gradient(30deg, blue, yellow);

Can add more colors:
background: linear-gradient(pink, blue, yellow);

If we don't want both colors to be 50-50:
background: linear-gradient(pink, yellow 20%);
=> YELLOW WILL START FROM 20% ONWARDS

To not have shadow effect must give it as:
background: linear-gradient(pink 50%, yellow 50%);

rgba: red green blue alpha

background: linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,0, 0.0), rgba(0,0,255, 1));

background: linear-gradient(to right, rgba(255,255,0, 0.0), rgba(0,0,255, 1));